-- South African Coal Export Prices Have Second Weekly Increase
-- B y   M a r e k   S t r z e l e c k i
-- 2012-04-03T08:30:27Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-03/south-african-coal-export-prices-have-second-weekly-increase.html
Coal export prices at  South Africa ’s
 Richards Bay , the continent’s biggest terminal for shipping the
fuel, increased for a second week.  Prices (CLSPSARB)  gained 22 cents, or 0.2 percent, to $103.42 a metric
ton in the week ended March 30, according to IHS McCloskey data
on Bloomberg. The price is quoted on a free-on-board basis,
which excludes delivery costs.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Marek Strzelecki in Warsaw at 
 mstrzelecki1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Lars Paulsson in London at 
 lpaulsson@bloomberg.net  